Rename variable 'lambda' README examples (#72)

`lambda` is a Python reserved word, so best practice is not to override it as it prevents its use later in the file. The syntax highlighting on GitHub is also showing it as a keyword which is a little confusing. I also commented the non-code lines so the examples are valid Python.
Bumping version number for new release.
Remove 3.7 target from .travis.yml file.
Added tests for pickle serialization.  Fixed a bug in file modes with pickle mode.  Updated copyright notice dates.  Fixed a couple of PEP8 nits.

Add support for pickle serialization (#53)

I have tested locally and all looks good.  I will create a separate issue to create a few more tests.
